    "path": "src/agent/task",
    "name": "task",
    "purpose": "Owns agent task runtime. Task drives the per-task worker thread: it sends the initial status, triggers the initial plan through Step, routes task, step, and execution events, and now routes plan events to plan_hub.route_event. TaskState stores session context, plan_hub, execution_map from ExecutionSignature to StepSignature, a monotonic step_count allocator that reserves contiguous step-number blocks, and the step WorkQueue, with a manual Debug impl. task_execution.rs starts execution steps, records execution_map entries, maps succeeding execution status back into StepEvent::Complete via Step, and starts execution-analysis plans by emitting PlanEvent::Trigger through Step::send_plan_event.",
